wikipedia_page.main: Arthur Collins (7 September 1871 – 22 July 1945) was an English cricketer active from 1895 to 1902 who played for Sussex. He appeared in 53 first-class matches as a righthanded batsman who bowled left-arm orthodox spin. He scored 1,812 runs with a highest score of 102 and took 36 wickets with a best performance of five for 61.
